{
  "stem": "11998.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you see, as I was saying, when we were out of the ghetto to go to work, the Nazis would come, and they would come into the ghetto and grab everybody that they found, so we built hiding places in our-- in our homes.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we lived in-- it was like a sixplex, an apartment building in Srodula, maybe it was three floors.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So maybe it was-- it was about six weeks apartments in there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I built with friends of mine a hiding place in the basement.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we built-- because it was quite small, we built another one above the roof space.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The building was in two stories, so we went through the hallway through an opening in the staircase to go into the roof space of the adjoining building.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we come in through the opening with a sandbox that you would pull away to get in there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then once you're in there, you lock it with hooks and bars to hold it rigid in there against the wall.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, it became useful when we were to-- when they finally-- it was August 1st, 1943 when they finally came for us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were home.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was Saturday night, and so they came in early Sunday morning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my sister was away to a party and she came home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Must have been after midnight.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was well after midnight.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had sentries-- sentries stand station on the roof to see what was happening.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because we knew that when there was a deportation from previous experience, we knew that the Gestapo headquarters, which was visible from our ghetto, all the lights would come on at 3 o'clock, or 4 o'clock, or 5 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we knew that something was happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
